        <delSpan spanTo="#e1-0047.01" rend="unnmarked"/>
        <line>And heard, <del rend="strikethrough">&amp; cried</del>, <del rend="strikethrough">ah
                woe is m</del>e!</line>
        <line>And died&#8212;as the mad as the <del rend="strikethrough">wild w</del>aves be</line>
        <line rend="center">3<hi rend="sup">.</hi>d</line>
        <line>[SKETCH IN INK OF CLOUDS OR TREES]</line>
        <line>By such dread words from Earth <unclear reason="illegible">t</unclear></line>
        <anchor xml:id="e1-0047.01"/>
        <line rend="center"><add><metamark function="separate"
                    >___________________________________</metamark></add></line>
        <!-- There's a line cutting through the text here, separating PU and ION, should
    we use metamark-separate or a top zone?-->
        <line>wrought his <del rend="strikethrough">poetry</del> poem. <milestone unit="tei:speaker"
                spanTo="#e1-0047.02"/><hi rend="underline">Ion</hi><anchor xml:id="e1-0047.02"/>
            Assured-ly</line>
        <line>o Socrates. <milestone unit="tei:speaker" spanTo="#e1-0047.03"/><mod>
                <del rend="overwritten"><hi rend="underline">Ion.</hi></del>
                <add place="intralinear">Soc.</add>
            </mod><anchor xml:id="e1-0047.03"/> And the other</line>
        <line>Poets do they not treat of the same</line>
        <line><unclear reason="case">m</unclear>atters?&#8212; <milestone unit="tei:speaker"
                spanTo="#e1-0047.04"/><hi rend="underline">Ion</hi><anchor xml:id="e1-0047.04"/>
            Certainly: but not like</line>
        <line>Homer. <milestone unit="tei:speaker" spanTo="#e1-0047.05"/><hi rend="underline"
                >Soc</hi>.<anchor xml:id="e1-0047.05"/> How, worse?&#8212; <milestone
                unit="tei:speaker" spanTo="#e1-0047.06"/>Ion.<anchor xml:id="e1-0047.06"/> Oh,
            far</line>
        <line>worse! <milestone unit="tei:speaker" spanTo="#e1-0047.07"/><hi rend="underline"
                >Soc</hi>.<anchor xml:id="e1-0047.07"/> And <add place="superlinear">is</add> Homer
                <add place="superlinear">much</add> better than they?&#8212;</line>
        <line><milestone unit="tei:speaker" spanTo="#e1-0047.08"/><hi rend="underline"
                >Ion</hi>.<anchor xml:id="e1-0047.08"/> Oh Jupiter, how much better! <milestone
                unit="tei:speaker" spanTo="#e1-0047.09"/><hi rend="underline">Soc</hi>.<anchor
                xml:id="e1-0047.09"/></line>
        <line><mod>
                <del rend="strikethrough">Still</del>
                <add place="superlinear"><unclear reason="illegible">Suppose</unclear></add>
            </mod>, my dear friend Ion, <mod>
                <del rend="strikethrough">a <unclear reason="illegible">man</unclear></del>
                <add place="sublinear">several</add>
            </mod></line>
        <line>persons are solving a problem a</line>
        <line>problem in arithmetic, an<retrace cause="clarify">d</retrace> one alone</line>
        <line>does it correctly: a man might</line>
        <line>know who had given the true answer.</line>
        <line><milestone unit="tei:speaker" spanTo="#e1-0047.10"/><hi rend="underline"
                >Ion</hi>.<anchor xml:id="e1-0047.10"/> Certainly. <milestone unit="tei:speaker"
                spanTo="#e1-0047.11"/><hi rend="underline">Soc</hi><anchor xml:id="e1-0047.11"
            />&#8212;The same as had</line>
        <line>been aware of those who had given</line>
        <line>the false one, or not? <milestone unit="tei:speaker" spanTo="#e1-0047.12"/><hi
                rend="underline">Ion</hi>.<anchor xml:id="e1-0047.12"/> The same</line>
        <line>clearly. <milestone unit="tei:speaker" spanTo="#e1-0047.13"/><hi rend="underline"
                >Soc</hi><anchor xml:id="e1-0047.13"/> That is, some one who understood</line>
